rComments: Really fun and interesting classes, especially tutorials. Hard to study for tests because the range of material is broad, but the actual tests are fair. Seems to really care about his students and the subject. Would take again.

Charly is hands down great. Really cares about his students and cares about your grade. He wants you not only to take interest in his class but he wants you to learn something. Tests and evals are straight forward but you need to study for them!

I took his class for ESS261, ESS241 and even ESS222. Overall, he is a pretty nice and easy prof. Although his lecture contents can be quite confusing, his tests are usually quite fair and is easy to get a B. With a little bit of work, an A is definitely possible.
Great Class, allowed cheat sheet for exams and questions weren't difficult although not easy either. Some lectures are extremely long though

Charly is one of the nicest professors at U of T. He made an effort to know our names and talk to us, and it's clear that he really cares about students. U of T needs more professors like him, however the negative comments below have some truth to them. He should speed up lectures, and work on lecture quality for sure. His class was very enjoyable.

BEYOND FANTASTIC!!! This course has been really exciting and has only made my love of geology grow. This prof is great - very knowledgeable, cares about his students like no other UofT prof! Only downfall is he does tend to speak a tad too quietly.

I am not harsh towards professor Bank, more so towards the course. The assignments were confusing and god knows how long it would take to contact a TA they made this course a living hell. Bank was passionate about the class but could speak louder and project his voice. The textbook in this class is your guide; you ain't getting anything from him.
Great guy!!!

MOST accommodating prof  I've ever had! Very helpful, really nice, and the first prof I've seen who genuinely cares about his students, and tries different approaches in lectures, which is fantastic. I've never seen a prof like that in UofT. If you're genuinely interested in something, Charly will help you reach it.

The worst prof I've ever had BY FAR. The 2 for easiness isn't because you have to study hard for a good grade, but rather because grading in the course is like a random lottery. Lectures were utterly useless and mind-numbingly dull. Tests made no sense. Even the department head couldn't figure out the answers to some of his midterm questions!

He's a terrible professor. I think he's the worst professor at UofT, and that takes some effort to earn that title! Basically, his slides are useless, the book is useless, and you don't learn anything, because he has very poor grammar and English skills as well, so lectures don't help!
God-Awful Professor, can't understand him, he makes grammatical mistakes on his tests and assignments, which actually changes the questions! Avoid him at all costs....(And I did well in the course)

Great professor and a clear lecturer. I found the material interesting and the class easy despite not taking otes (and I'm not a science student). His multiple choice questions are tricky, but the assignment is RIDICULOUSLY easy, so that helps boost marks. The only downside was the tutorials, which were boring. Overall, I'd recommend Prof Bank. :)

Boring powerpoint lectures.  Useless readings.  Terrible TA's. Poorly explained assignments.  Ridiculously hard final exam.  Stupid little multiple choice questions of tidbits easily missed in weekly readings.  I cannot stress enough how bad the TA's were.  They made everything 10 times more difficult.  Do not take this class if he is the Prof.
Lectures were unclear and boring. test/exams were badly worded. some Prof. Banks's TAs were highly unqualify
didnt teach us anything, but then expected us to know it all for tests.

I've never met such an incompetent lecturer! His lectures consist of reading out his lecture slides v-e-r-y s-l-o-w-l-y. Is incapable of explaining any concept clearly. Tried to bring down the class average by marking down assignments for no reason and giving out exam questions that had nothing to do with material covered in class or in the text.
Very interactive and motivating! Prof. Bank teaches with great enthusiasm and is a fair marker. I enjoyed this science course.

Very disorganized professor. I think he sometimes forgets that we don't have a Geology background - tends to go on about stuff that's way too advanced. (Fortunately, his midterm only covers the easy stuff). However, his enthusiasm is contagious - he got me really interested in the subject. The field trip was fun. And I agree with the cute comment.
Such a nice professor. Explains concepts well and gives so much clues about his term tests. Great class to take!
He is such a nice guy, and what a cutie! He's adorable and explains concepts with care.
He is a nice and helpful professor. Some students are so lazy. He is good.
No textbook, no lecture slides, very disorganized. I'm sure he knows his stuff. He just can't present it well.
I like the accent.  Kind of an effeminate Arnold Schwarzenegger.  He makes me smile.

His inexperience is very evident and is by far one of the worst professors I have ever had at UofT.  In particular, he has a poor lecturing style in which he seemingly manages to stretch twenty minutes of material into two hours.
